# What is Java?

Java is a high-level, object-oriented, class-based programming language developed by Sun Microsystems in 1995.

It is now maintained by Oracle Corporation.

Java is one of the most widely used programming languages for building enterprise applications.

---

# History of Java

- 1991 - Project Green started.
- Developed by James Gosling and his team.
- Original name: Oak.
- Renamed to Java.
- Released in 1995 by Sun Microsystems.
- Oracle Corporation acquired Sun Microsystems in 2010 and now maintains Java.

---

# Why was Java Created?

Java was originally created to develop software for consumer electronic devices.

Later, because of its platform independence, security, and robustness, it became one of the most popular languages for enterprise software, web applications, cloud services, and backend development.

---

# Write Once, Run Anywhere (WORA)

One of Java's biggest advantages is platform independence.

Execution Flow

.java

↓

javac

↓

.class (Bytecode)

↓

JVM

↓

Machine Code

↓

CPU

The same bytecode can run on any operating system that has a compatible JVM.

---

# Features of Java

## 1. Simple

- Easy to learn
- Cleaner syntax than C++

---

## 2. Object-Oriented

Everything in Java is organized using classes and objects.

Main OOP concepts:

- Encapsulation
- Inheritance
- Polymorphism
- Abstraction

(These will be covered later.)

---

## 3. Platform Independent

The same bytecode runs on different operating systems using JVM.

---

## 4. Secure

Java provides security through:

- Bytecode Verification
- No direct memory manipulation
- Automatic memory management

---

## 5. Robust

Java is reliable because of:

- Exception Handling
- Garbage Collection

---

## 6. Portable

The same Java program works across different operating systems.

---

## 7. Multithreaded

Java supports multiple threads running simultaneously.

---

## 8. High Performance

Java uses Just-In-Time (JIT) Compilation to improve execution speed.

