# What is an Algorithm?

An Algorithm is a finite sequence of well-defined steps used to solve a problem.

Programming is not about memorizing code.

Programming is about designing efficient algorithms.

---

# Real-Life Algorithm Example

Algorithm to Make Tea

Step 1 - Boil Water

Step 2 - Add Tea Powder

Step 3 - Add Milk

Step 4 - Add Sugar

Step 5 - Stir

Step 6 - Serve Tea

Every task can be broken into step-by-step instructions.

---

# Software Algorithm Example

User clicks Login

↓

Receive Username & Password

↓

Validate Input

↓

Search User in Database

↓

Compare Password

↓

Generate JWT Token

↓

Send Response

This is an example of an algorithm used in software.

