# Important Definitions

## Java

A high-level, object-oriented, class-based programming language.

---

## WORA

Write Once, Run Anywhere.

The same Java bytecode can execute on different operating systems using JVM.

---

## Bytecode

Intermediate code generated by the Java compiler.

---

## JVM

Java Virtual Machine that converts bytecode into machine code.

---

## Algorithm

A finite sequence of well-defined steps used to solve a problem.

