# Commands You Should Know

## Check Java Version

```bash
java -version
```

Displays the installed Java Runtime version.

---

## Check Java Compiler Version

```bash
javac -version
```

Displays the installed Java compiler version.

---

## View Environment Variable (Windows)

```cmd
echo %JAVA_HOME%
```

Shows the Java installation path if JAVA_HOME is configured.

(We'll configure this properly in the next lesson.)

